DOC.HEAD: URGENT
U.S. Officer Shoots Panama Corporal in 2nd Shooting Incident
Eds: LEADS with six grafs to UPDATE with second incident involving U.S., Panama, details. Picks up 2nd pvs, `American soldiers ...' Minor editing to trim
DOC.TEXT: An American officer shot and wounded a Panamanian corporal today near a U.S. installation, a Southern Command official said. It was the second shooting incident in three days between U.S. and Panamanian forces. The official, who spoke to The Associated Press on condition of anonymity, said the incident occurred near a laundry on the western edge of Panama City and the Southern Command headquarters.
